description:
Nokoru, Akira, Suo and the seven seals arrive at a fountain in the center of Clamp School. Nokoru asks Kamui to put his hand on the symbol of the school. Kamui does it and a secret passage is opened. They go in. At the approach of the zone of seal, the other sacred sword liberates itself and asks Nataku to bring it back to Kamui. Nokoru explains that Clamp School was built star-shaped in order to seal the sacred sword. He tells him also that Kamui must seal his sacred sword in order to seal the other sacred sword. Kamui remembers what Subaru said and then accepts to seal his sacred sword. Whereas Kamui seals it, Nataku steals the other one to bring it to Fuma.

Kanoe has another conversation with her sister. She scoffs at Hinoto saying that the second Kamui is awake and there is only one future. Beast detects the arrival of Fuma and Kakyo. Beast confirms it is Kamui. Kanoe welcomes Fuma as Kamui.

Whereas the dragons of Earth bring together, Kamui decides to see Hinoto in order to have some answers. Hinoto has a conversation with Kakyo. He reveals he knows that Hinoto brought together the dragon of Heaven in order to modify the future for her own interest. He shows him the last vision of Kotori. Fuma introduces himself and Kakyo to others. Satsuki informs that the last three angels come there with the sacred sword.



Hien, Sohi and Daisuke are worried about their mistress’s health when Kamui arrives. Hinoto brings him to a dream. Kamui asks her why his mother is dead. Hinoto shows the past. Toru requires Saya to leave Togakushi Shrine in order to save her life. Saya refuses saying she is ready to die for Toru. Kyogo, his husband, reveals he knows that Saya doesn’t love him, but she loves Toru. Kyogo accepts to protect the sacred sword for Kamui. Fuma is present. He dares at his mother’s head and leaks her blood. In present time, Hinoto reveals that Kotori’s destiny was foreordained: she would be dead even if Kamui chooses to be an angel. Hinoto reveals also that Toru was the kagenie of the Earth. Her death is due to global warming. It is at this moment that Kakyo appears. He shows him the two possible futures: the rebirth of the Earth in case of the victory of the Dragons of Earth or the death of the Earth due to global warming in case of the victory of the Dragons of Heaven. Kamui wakes up, but he still wish to bring back Fuma.
name: Fugue

description: The adventure in the '40s continues! It’s a day in the life of the Golden Age Wonder Woman, as the disguised, time-displaced Diana tries to track down a Nazi saboteur in Washington D.C.!
name: Her Daughter's Mother

description:
Wonder Woman is trying to track down the male Cheetah, while Troia is still on the trail of Angle Man. Their two quests come together when they uncover Barbara Minerva, the original female Cheetah, who is harnessing the power of the Furies for revenge.

Sebastian Ballesteros has stolen Cheetah's powers and she's on the prowl to find him. Diana interrogates Circe who is held on Paradise Island.
name: Revenge of the Cheetah - Part One: The Hunt for Sebastian Ballesteros

description: Wonder Woman, Wonder Girl and Troia are caught in the middle of the male Cheetah and the Fury-powered female Cheetah, as they ferociously fight in Brazil!
name: Revenge of the Cheetah - Part Two: A Cat-God Scorned

description: It's the end of an era, as writer/artist Phil Jimenez bids a fond farewell to Wonder Woman - in a "Day in the Life" issue that will bring a smile to longtime Wonder Woman fans! And as we get further insight into the life of Trevor Barnes, will he end up as Wonder Woman's new beau?
name: Wonder Boys

description: Walter Simonson, Jerry Ordway and P. Craig Russell join cover artist Adam Hughes for an incredible 6-part adventure! Wonder Woman has vanished without a trace. Bereft of her memories, deprived of her gods-given abilities, and without her familiar costume, lasso and bracelets, Diana must fight off a horde of monstrous foes and find her way back to Earth from the Cryptocombs - the Cemetery of the Gods - all the while protecting a mysterious clay statue of a baby girl.
name: The Game of the Gods - Part One: Figure of Earth

description:
"The Game of the Gods" continues as an amnesiac Wonder Woman struggles to regain her memory! Returned to the streets of New York and hunted by unexpected adversaries, only Diana's innate skills enable her to survive. Will a devoted fan provide the answers she needs? And why does Wonder Woman adopt yet another new look?

Diana is still trying to repiece her memory and she gets help from a Wonder Woman fan named Becca Doherty.
name: The Game of the Gods - Part Two: Red Eyes in the Morning...

description: Wonder Woman returns to Themyscira to find some answers while Trevor Barnes is in Zambia trying to figure out why he was sent there.
name: The Game of the Gods - Part Three: Deities and Demons...!

description: "The Game of the Gods" heats up as Wonder Woman faces off against a goddess, one who shouldn't even exist! Plus, Diana and Trevor Barnes learn more about the Shattered God and how his plans threaten the future of the universe itself!
name: The Game of the Gods - Part Four: Sister's Sorrow

description: "The Game of the Gods" nears its fateful conclusion as the Shattered God strikes closer and closer to the Amazon princess! But what is this nigh-unstoppable being's ultimate goal? And will Diana prove an unwitting pawn in his plan?
name: The Game of the Gods - Part Five: The Passion of Diana!

description: "The Game of the Gods" concludes! At the center of the universe, the ancient threat known as the Shattered God stands on the brink of bending all existence to his will. Restored to full power, Diana learns the secret behind her recent transformation, but will it be enough to turn the battle? Or will an unexpected champion be forced to make an incredible sacrifice?
name: The Game of the Gods - Part Six: The Passion of Trevor!

description:
While Wonder Woman fights to capture the brutal dictator of an African nation, a new hire at the Themysciran Embassy discovers just how enormous Diana's mission truly is.

It's Jonah McCarthy's first day on the job. There's a bit of orientation on his new duties (lawyer and handler to Wonder Woman), a tour of the office (the Themysciran embassy), introductions to his new co-workers and even a stop down in the kitchen to meet the company's chef (a minotaur of course). He gets to meet one of his new boss's friends, Superman, when he drops of a manuscript he's finished reading for Diana. Then it's time to meet the boss... Wonder Woman. And, as is tradition when you work for Diana, his first day isn't complete until she's taken him flying.
name: The Mission

description:
"Down to Earth" part 1! The project Wonder Woman has been working on since her arrival in Patriarch's World is finally revealed, giving new ammunition to Diana's foes, on Earth and Olympus itself.

Wonder Woman releases her new book about her views on Earth, and some aren't too happy with her opinions. A new villian, who has no superpowers, but is intent on ruining Wonder Woman's reputation.
name: Down to Earth - Part One

description:
The Flash makes a cameo appearance in Part 2 of the incendiary 5-part story "Down to Earth!" Touring to promote her long-anticipated project, Diana encounters a raging forest fire - but why does she refuse the help of the Fastest Man Alive? And one of Wonder Woman's greatest foes makes an unexpected appearance on Themyscira…but what is he doing there?

A forest fire has erupted and instead of working together, Flash and Wonder Woman argue over which is best to douse it. Veronica Cale is still on continuing on with her plan.
name: Down to Earth - Part Two

description:
As the gods themselves respond to Wonder Woman's book, Diana's earthbound foes mount offensives of their own. While her allies attempt to protect her reputation, Wonder Woman makes the shocking discovery that one of her dearest friends has been abducted.

Vanessa Cale is almost finished with her plan to destroy Wonder Woman's reputation, while Wonder Woman's book staff is fighting aginst the prejudice.
name: Down to Earth - Part Three

description:
Diana confronts her greatest enemy face-to-face! And while conflict on Olympus threatens to shake the foundations of Wonder Woman's life, mortal forces conspire to bring her down once and for all.

A double sized issue where Wonder Woman confronts Silver Swan and Veronica Cale's plan rears its ugly head. The leader of the opposition of Diana's book is shot, and Cale plans to pin the murder on Wonder Woman.
name: Down to Earth - Part Four

description:
As Veronica Cale unleashes an upgraded version of one of Diana's deadliest foes, Ares' machinations on Olympus cause an astonishing change to the lives of all the Amazons of Themyscira! Plus, excerpts from Wonder Woman's book, a retelling of an ancient myth, a Golden Age-style WW story, and more!

Wonder Woman and Silver Swan battle it out, while Hera's jealousy gets the better of her and accuses Zeus of his wandering eye for the Amazons. As revenge, she sends the floating islands of Themyscira down to the sea.
name: Down to Earth - Part Five

description: Because of Hera's rage from the last issue, Diana has to deal with it, not to mention hundreds of visitors that have gone down with the island. Meanwhile, Circe escapes from the island and is helped out by Stheno and Euryale and resurrect Medusa.
name: Ripples

description: This issue is focused on Wonder Woman's new villain, Veronica Cale. Cale's plan to pin the murder on Wonder Woman didn't work out too well. Cale suspects that Diana's staff have managed to prevent her plan from happening and this allows Cale to recount her history to the mole, Kimberley Dunn and why she hates Wonder Woman so much.
name: Leaks

description: Paradise Island had re-situated itself over the Coast of Carolinas and the US government isn't too happy. Diana calls Batman to help her solve the murder of Darrel Keyes.
name: Bitter Pills - Part One

description: Circe is working on Medusa, and Wonder Woman and Batman are close to finding the killer of Darrel Keyes.
name: Bitter Pills - Part Two

description: Wonder Woman confirms her suspicions about Dr. Psycho's involvement with Veronica Cale, while Medusa has been successfully resurrected and plans to kill Wonder Woman.
name: Bitter Pills - Part Three

description:
When a newspaper offers a reward for Wonder Woman's secret identity several likely candidates rise to the fore only to be targeted by the underworld. Wonder Woman must find a way to prevent further attacks without revealing her secret identity.
 
Luria, a young amazon wins a contest which entitles her to have any wish granted. She asks to leave Paradise Island and join Wonder Woman's in man's world even though any amazon who sets foot in man's world loses her immortality. Wonder Woman must find a way to dissuade her.
 
Wonder Woman goes to nursing school as a way to promote young women to go into nursing however the head of the school seems to have some grudge against Wonder Woman.
name: The Amazing Impersonation

description:
1. "The Crime Master of Time"
  2. "The Wonder Woman Nobody Knows"
  3. "Wonder Women of History" featuring Martha G. Kimball. Reprinted in Girls' Love Stories #46 and Superman's Girl Friend, Lois Lane #106.
  4. "Fashions of the Far East" two page text piece.
  5. "The Secret Treasure At Rainbow's End"
name: The Crime Master of Time / The Wonder Woman Nobody Knows / The Secret Treasure At Rainbow's End

description:
Wonder Woman looks into the disappearance of a secret new bomber and stumbles onto the mystery of a ghost train.  
 
Wonder Woman must prevent a game of cosmic chess from destroying the Earth.
 
Wonder Woman uncovers a Venusian plot to drown the Earth and must find a way to stop it before the next rainfall.
name: Ghost Train
The Man Who Shook The Earth

description:
Wonder Woman finds her self under attack by strange invisible forces which are destroying her effectiveness as a crime fighter. She must determine the orgin of these attacks before her career and reputation are damaged beyond repair.

Wonder Woman is invited to attend Leprechaun college with the catch that if she passes the college will cease to exist and her amazon pride will not allow her to fail on purpose. Wonder Woman must find a way to both succeed and fail at the same time.

A rich skinflint sets a challenge for Wonder Woman. If she can turn a penny into a million dollars in 24 hours he will match that million in a donation to Wonder Woman's charity.
name: Wonder Woman's Invisible Twin

description:
Wonder Woman travels 10 years into a future where another world war threatens to destroy all of civilization then returns to prevent the war from happening in the first place.

 

The tale of how Wonder Woman came to be known as being "Beautiful as Aphrodite, Wise as Athena, Swifter than Mercury, and Stronger than Hercules."

 

Diana Prince wins a date with Steve Trevor. While on her date she is forced to take action as Wonder Woman on numerous occasions without Steve Trevor catching on to her dual identity.
name: The War That Never Happened

description:
Steve Trevor and Diana Prince investigate a series of mysterious disappearances. When Steve Trevor disappears right before her eyes Wonder Woman's desparate search uncovers a plot to destroy the earth as she knows it.
 
When Hippolyta suddenly falls into a death like sleep Wonder Woman must find a cure or she will be forced to return to Paradise Island and rule in her mother's place. But the search for a cure soon places Wonder Woman at risk of sharing her mother's fate.
 
When Wonder Woman accepts a position as stunt woman in a movie she soon learns that she has replaced a professional stunt man at the last minute. Determined to help him get his big break she convinces the studio to go ahead with him as the stunt man. However when he has trouble with the difficult stunts she must help him succeed while remaining unseen.
name: Wonder Woman - Hollywood Stunt Queen!

description:
A band of criminals come up with a plan to discover Wonder Woman's secret identity but they net three girls including Diana Prince. Certain that one of the three must be Wonder Woman they decide to kill all three girls to insure they succeed in killing Wonder Woman. Now Wonder Woman must protect the other two girls as well as herself while preventing the criminals from discovering her true secret identity.

Wonder Woman recieves a call for help from the king of the leprechauns. Their magic lamp has gone out and all the leprechauns have been left powerless and are falling into a permenant sleep. Wonder Woman must refill the lamp with flame from the sun and cosmic dust from Halley's comet. But can even Wonder Woman perform such an incredible feat.

The story of the origin of Wonder Woman’s earrings and the function they serve.
name: Wonder Woman's Triple Identity!

description:
Wonder Woman battles the Human Tank a supercriminal who's incredibly hard skin makes him impervious to bullets.

When Wonder Woman mysteriously awakens in San Francisco with no memory of how she got there she seemingly finds herself unable to leave. She soon finds the cause only to find herself facing a martian invasion and the devious Duke of Deception.

Wonder Woman happens upon a book that contains a picture of her as a queen from 400 years ago leading her to travel through time to unravel the mystery of how this came to pass.
name: The Secret Invasion

description:
Wonder Woman battles a series of monsters that escape from a 3D film.

 

Gangland stages a bogus parade in Wonder Woman's honour releasing sleeping gas from the balloons so they can rob the city at their leisure. Wonder Woman must find a way escape their trap and stop their scheme.

 

The criminal Thought Master traps Wonder Woman in a world of illusion where none of her accessories function. To escape her illusory prison she must find the one thing in it that isn't an illusion.
name: The 3-D Terror!

description:
Diana Prince's double turns out to be an enemy spy. Once she is captures Steve Trevor and General Darnell convince Diana Prince to masquerade as her double to trap the leader of the spy network.
 
Wonder Woman and Steve Trevor visit a gallery containing portraits of her performing impossible feats. The gallery owner offers to donate $10000 to charity for each of the feats that she is able to duplicate. However someone doesn't want her to succeed and turns every attempted feat into a deathtrap.

When Wonder Woman catches a meteor, in order to prevent it from crashing to the earth, touching it makes her anti-magnetic preventing her from touching anyone or anything.
name: Confessions of a Spy!

description:
Wonder Woman investigates the Volcano prophet a man who seems to be able to predict when a volcano will explode and is forcing people to pay him to warn them.

Angle Man develops a plan to reveal Wonder Woman's secret identity by making her footprints phosphorescent.

Criminals plot to ruin the wedding of Wonder Woman and Steve Trevor
name: The Volcano Maker

description:
Wonder Woman must defend her right to remain princess of the amazons by completing a series of challenges. These challenges include a series of competitions against other Amazons while severely handicapped and two seemingly impossible tasks.

Criminals posing as a legitimate businessmen offer to give 1 million dollars to charity if Wonder Woman reveals her secret identity. Wonder Woman wrestles with the moral dilemma of whether or not she can refuse the offer.

Wonder Woman must rescue her leprechaun friends who have been shrunk by an evil leprechaun.
name: The Winning of Wonder Woman's Tiara
The Bird Who Revealed Wonder Woman's Identity!
The Island That Wonder Woman Built!

description:
Headmistress Gates is is trouble. Her school must meet another school in a baseball game with the losing school to be merged with the winning school. However due to a measles epidemic there are no students in her school. She calls upon Wonder Woman for help but in order for Wonder Woman to be allowed to play for her school she must consent to allow the headmaster of the other school to set the rules of the competition at will. He continually sets seeminly impossible tasks for Wonder Woman.

According to amazon law one day of every year Wonder Woman's weapons lose their special properties without any advance warning. She must battle the odds to continue to fight crime without the benefit of her braclets, tiara and lasso of truth.

Wonder Woman is offered 1 million dollars for charity if she shoots a movie starring herself with a mysterious script.
name: Andy Gorilla - Prize Pupil!

description:
An underworld scientist known as Spider shrinks Wonder Woman to the size of a flea. Wonder Woman then finds herself in a flea circus where the fleas have been trained to react to her as if she were a dangerous animal. She must find away to escape and return to her normal size.

 

Wonder Woman rescues a plane that wanders into a nuclear test only to be contaminated by radiation. While it cannot harm her she is now a danger to everyone around her.

 

When the governor's car and escort disappear Wonder Woman must investigate their disappearance and rescue the governor.
name: The Amazon Flea Circus!

description:
Wonder Woman falls asleep near a pond only to awaken wearing a strange mask that will not come off. She soon realizes that the mask contains a time bomb. A danger to everyone around her she must find a way to remove the mask before it explodes.


The story of how Wonder Woman won her invisible plane.

When Wonder Woman receives and SOS from Saturn she and Steve Trevor attempt to prevent the invasion of Saturn by people from its moon Titan.
name: The Mask of Mystery!

description:
1. "The Dream Dooms"
  2. "Three Secret Wishes"
  3. "Women of Distinction" one panel biography of Mrs. Harriet Maxwell Converse, Blanche Stuart Scott, Susanna Salter and Hannah Adams. Reprinted in Wonder Woman #126 and Superman's Girl Friend, Lois Lane #106.
  4. "What Does Your Name Mean?" two page text piece.
  5. "The Vanishing Criminal"
name: The Dream Dooms! / Three Secret Wishes / The Vanishing Criminal

description:
Wonder Woman travels back through time to aid Robin Hood in escaping from Nottingham Castle.

 

Steve Trevor learns about Wonder Woman's Amazon ring which will only be visible to him when there is no crime or injustice and Wonder Woman is free to marry him. Wonder Woman's brief visit to an world without crime causes the ring to appear on Diana Prince's forcing her to all sorts of different strategies to prevent Steve from learning her secret identity.

 

Wonder Woman loses her voice leaving her unable to control her invisible plane just as she is set to fly a crucial shipment of medicine to the artic.
name: Wonder Woman Meets Robin Hood

description:
A flying saucer lands with only a child inside leaving Wonder Woman with the mystery of where the child came from and how to return the child to its parents.

Wonder Woman helps a doctor to outdo her chauvinistic male co-workers.

Wonder Woman must save the people of the blue dimension from invaders from the orange dimension. Her trip to the blue dimension is given as explanation for why Wonder Woman's hair is blue.
name: The Flying Ambulance

description:
Angle Man reveals his latest secret weapon against Wonder Woman. His own Wonder Woman.

When Wonder Woman investigates the sudden appearance of a large statue of her she finds herself transported to a world of illusion created by the Duke of Deception. To escape she must find the one thing that is real in this world in less than an hour.

Wonder Woman must destroy an indestructible tree from space before it shatters the world.
name: The Secret Wonder Woman!
The Painting That Betrayed Wonder Woman

description:
After completing a mission under the ocean Wonder Woman returns to the surface to find that the world seems to be  frozen in time.

When Steve Rogers' plane crashes on an uncharted island Wonder Woman must rescue him from an island with giant dangers.

Wonder Woman attends a birthday party for her thrown by a group of poor little girls who give her a paper tiara they have made. When the wind blows it away Wonder Woman must rescue it from a series of dangers that threaten to destroy it.
name: Island of the Giants

description:
Everywhere she goes Wonder Woman finds a box with a warning not to open it. Emergencies continue to prevent her from opening the box which disappears before she can return to it.

 

Wonder Woman's Lasso tells a series of stories about adventures where it played an important role in the story.

 

A billionaire offers one million dollars to anyone who discovers Wonder Woman’s secret identity which leads Wonder Woman to suffer extreme anxiety.
name: Mystery of the Vanishing Box
The Master of Earth's Twin Worlds

description:
Wonder Woman competes in an interplanetary Olympics against her counterparts from Mercury, Venus and Jupiter.

 

Wonder Woman tells the story of why there is an eagle on her costume.

 

Wonder Woman encounters a statue of her built in honour of feats she performed a few days ago. Feats she cannot remember.
name: The Eagle Who Caged People

description:
Queen Hippolyta goes missing while out for a swim. Now Wonder Woman must find her before the amazons force her to take the throne.

 

A Martian invasion force under the command of the Duke of Deception shrinks Skyscraper City to the size of a dollhouse. Wonder Woman has to find a way to defeat the Martians despite her new diminutive size before they shrink the rest of the world.

 

Wonder Woman helps a little boy who like to play King Arthur overcome the ridicule of his peers.
name: Menace of the Mermen
Wonder Woman - the World's Most Dangerous Human

description: Wonder Woman's origin story and character was given a Silver Age revamp in this issue. Rober Kanigher's story retold how the contest that had been initiated by Athena and sponsored by Hippolyta would determine which Amazon would be sent to live in "Man's world." Orana, the red-haired Amazon challenged Diana for the title of Wonder Woman. Her challenge was unsuccessful and Diana returned to live among men, taking the identity of Diana Prince as she did so, becoming secretary to Steve Trevor, an army intelligence officer.
name: The Million Dollar Penny

description: The Wonder Woman of another dimension comes to Paradise Island to challenge Diana to a competition.
name: The Forest of Giants
The Three Faces of Wonder Woman

description:
Who is Wonder Woman? Where did she come from? How did she obtain her invincible powers? So many times have these questions been asked-and the time has come to release the answers!

Hippolyta and a newly born Diana are visited by four gods bearing gifts. Aphrodite gives Diana the gift of beauty, and Athena the gift of wisdom. Impressed with her speed Mercury gifts her with speed greater than his own and Hercules makes her stronger than he is. Years later a teenage Diana travels with the rest of the Amazons who flee the wars of man’s world. During their voyage they encounter man perils and it falls to Diana to rescue them and bring them safely to Paradise Island where she continues as their protector.

When pictures taken by a rocket show the existence of dinosaurs in space Steve Rogers investigates. Wonder Woman follows him to ensure his safe return.
name: The Eagle of Space

description:
The space giant Tooroo claims the earth as his plaything and attacks on the same day that Wonder Woman’s weapons lose there special properties for a day.

 

The amazons begin to suspect that something is wrong with young Diana when she suddenly becomes impossible to photograph.
name: The Human Charm Bracelet

description:
All is chaos in the Rosewell Sanitarium in Charles, Massachusetts. Devil-Slayer battles the incarnations of his personal demons, while the fellow inmates of his alter ego, Eric Simon Payne, panic. The staff try to lead the patients out to safety, but they look out the doors to find the whole building is floating in another dimension. Mr. Termineus, in his Santa suit, oversees the mayhem. Finally, Sorrow, the mute telepathic inmate, calms Eric, and the demons dissipate.

On Earth, Ellen Brandt and the Man-Thing stand at the pit which seems to have engulfed the asylum. The voices of the mystic staff Ellen carries overwhelm her, and she drops it. The Man-Thing picks it up, and the voices begin to speak through him. The words of the ancient voices encourage Ellen, so she again takes the staff and the pair vanish from the corporeal world.

Meanwhile, the Jack and Gwyneth Burke decorate their Brooklyn home for Christmas Eve, but Jack is briefly haunted by a vision of Termineus. In another room, their son, Job, is awakened by a visit from the spirit of Sorrow, whom he recognizes. She gives him a sense of well-being as a gift.

In the asylum, Termineus confronts Sorrow for visiting Job, but Devil-Slayer attacks him and Termineus fades away. Sorrow and Eric realize time has frozen around them as they are joined by Man-Thing and Ellen, who herself was an inmate of Rosewell after being burned by the swamp monster. Ellen recognizes Sorrow, but their reunion is cut short when Devil-Slayer mistakes Man-Thing for another demon and attacks him, tearing him apart. During his frenzy, Eric recalls the events that led to him becoming the Devil-Slayer. He again collapses into a catatonic state as Sorrow tries to comfort him, while Termineus reappears. Though the voices of the staff call to Ellen to take action, she remains rooted to the spot, overwhelmed by the memories of her stay at Rosewell. Finally, the Man-Thing, who has reassembled himself into a misshapen mass, rises, and Devil-Slayer recovers to attack him again. The Man-Thing embraces Devil-Slayer and they burst into flames.
name: Silent Night

description:
Mr. Termineus converses with Job, the boy he'd abducted from his adoptive parents, Jack and Gwyneth Burke.  Job, knowing Termineus from his dreams, calmly accepts the situation, as the pair materialize in a mall where they turn toward an ice cream parlor. 
Meanwhile, in the Florida swamp, the Man-Thing and Ellen Brandt are confronted by the Cult of Entropy, who have in their clutches Howard the Duck.  Howard squirms free and implores the swamp creature to do something.  But before the Man-Thing can react, the cultists ensnare him in a coil of electric energy which constricts and slices him into chunks.  Ellen runs deeper into the swamp, carrying the staff of K'ad-Mon, until she is stopped in her tracks by an strange inhuman being. 
Later, at the cultist's camp, Howard suffers from extreme nausea, while around him the pieces of the Man-Thing lie in plastic bags.  The various piles of muck come to life, squeezing out of the bags, and join to reconstitute the creature, who then approaches Howard.  The cult leader, a severely scarred man calling himself Mahapralaya, also comes close, explaining the aims of the Cult of Entropy are to see to it that the shattered Nexus of All Realities is not repaired, so as to bring about the end of existence.  The way they intend to ensure that is to cut out the Nexus fragment that has lodged itself within Howard's body.  Then, unexpectedly, the Man-Thing begins forcing his substance down the Duck's throat.
Meanwhile, in their Brooklyn home, the Burkes report the disappearance of Job to a police detective.  When Gwyneth catches a glimpse of Job and Termineus in a mirror, she realizes that the mysterious entity has taken their son. 
Back in the swamp, Mahapralaya presides over the ritual during which he intends to slit open Howard's belly to access the Nexus fragment.  However, the Duck regurgitates the muck that coalesces in to the Man-Thing, who, now merged with the fragment, grows to gigantic proportions.  He takes up Mahapralaya in his hand, and the cult leader begins to burn.  But rather than a consuming flame, it acts as a cleansing energy.  Mahapralaya recalls the hard, soul-crushing life he's lived as the the fire renews him, making his body whole again.  Confused, but with a newfound hope, the leader and his acolytes take their leave. 
Soon, the Man-Thing shrivels into a desiccated form and lies immobile.  Howard tries to haul the lifeless swamp beast to get him some help, but doesn't get far before collapsing.  Weak from his ordeal with the Cult, Howard blacks out.  He comes to a short time later to find himself face to winged ankle with Namor the Sub-Mariner.
name: The Duck & the Muck

description:
An antediluvian god named Evenor has transformed Ellen Brandt into a water-breather and brought her to the depths of the Atlantic Ocean. Evenor has something vital for her to learn.

In the Florida swamps, Howard the Duck tries to move the desiccated mass of vegetation that was, until a short time before, the Man-Thing. He is confronted by Namor the Sub-Mariner, who has come to seek out the Man-Thing in response to a call by Neptune. While Namor was meditating, the sea god told him the survival of Atlantis, as well as all the worlds, depends on the aid of the swamp creature. As Howard explains how the Man-Thing 'died', the beast unexpectedly revives, thanks to the fragment from the shattered Nexus of All Realities retrieved from the Duck. Howard decides to get going while the getting is good.

The staff of K'ad Mon, lying nearby, rises and calls to the Man-Thing, who grasps it, allowing the voices of the spirits within it to speak through the creature.

Elsewhere, Mr. Termineus and Job Burke discuss the music of the spheres and Job's place in the cosmos. Termineus tells him the town of Serling where Job's biological parents Ellen and Ted Sallis (the human side of the Man-Thing) found themselves recently, was a dream created by Job. He goes on to say that Job is the latest in a lineage of such cosmic dreamers. While Job cries that he wants to go home, his adoptive parents, Jack and Gwyneth, come to believe clues to their abducted son's whereabouts lie in the Everglades where, a few weeks earlier, they had run into the Man-Thing. They soon take their leave of Brooklyn and head for Florida.

In the swamp, the staff, acting through the Man-Thing, opens a portal, through which the muck-monster and Namor pass. The staff transforms Man-Thing into a more seaworthy form, and soon the pair arrive, to the Sub-Mariner's astonishment, at the City of the Golden Gate, a legendary part of ancient Atlantis, heretofore thought to be lost forever. They are greeted by the amphibious Ellen, who tells them Evenor has brought her here to persuade them not to retrieve the Nexus fragment within the city.

She leads them into a temple, where they view the fragment mounted upon the Cloak of Cleito, the mother goddess of Atlantis. Namor wonders how the jewel which, according to legend, has always been attached to the cloak, could possibly be a piece of the recently shattered Nexus. Evenor appears and explains that the nature of the fragment is to exist outside time and space. He goes on to say the shrine must not be desecrated. The voice of the staff, however, reminds Namor that the fate of the multiverse depends on the fragments being returned to repair the Nexus. Namor makes his decision: the jewel will remain on the shrine of Cleito.

In response, the staff compels the Man-Thing to release its mystic forces, but Evenor counters the ploy by transforming the swamp creature back into a very shocked and confused Ted Sallis.
name: In the Waters of Eternity - Part One

description:
Overview

The unbelievable Baroness story continues! She’s confronted all that have betrayed her, except for one… but on the trail of her last target, her path crosses with another from her past: Flint returns! But is he going to stop her quest for revenge or help her with it?
name: Sins of the Mother, Part 3

description: This Christmas issue leads Spiderman to reflect on the losses of his Aunt May and the loss of his child in the delivery room with his wife, Mary Jane. On setting to a Daily Bugle mission to report of a mutant psychic in Central Park, Spiderman gains unlikely counseling by an extra-dimensional mutant known as Nate Grey a.k.a. X-Man.
name: T'was The Night Before Christmas

description: As a global wave of terror reaches its climactic peak, Tony Stark’s ability to lead S.H.I.E.L.D. is called into question by the powers-that-be. Can he trust even those closest to him within S.H.I.E.L.D., or is he exposing himself and the world to an even greater, more unspeakable threat from the villain behind the worldwide carnage?
name: Director Of S.H.I.E.L.D., Part 3

description:
Aliens take mental control of Wonder Woman's body and force her to commit crimes leading to her becoming a wanted woman.

 

Wonder Woman must find a way to be in two places at once when Wonder Woman and Diana Prince are given separate missions for military intelligence. In addition during these missions she will be carrying specials stamps depicting her greatest feats but unknown to anyone in military intelligence they have been treated with a chemical which will make them explode.
name: Wanted - Wonder Woman!

description:
When Paradise Island comes under attack by rockets a young Diana investigates to learn that the rockets are actually firecrackers that are being launched by giants. The giants agree to cease their entertainment only if Diana succeeds in performing a series of feats that none of the Giants have been able to accomplish.

A group of criminals offer Wonder Woman one million dollars if she reveals her secret identity which leads to a rash of young women who endanger themselves attempting to prove that they are Wonder Woman. The forces the real Wonder Woman to risk her secret identity to flush out the culprits.
name: Wonder Girl in Giant Land

description: A large fleet of flying saucers threaten to attack the earth if their princess is not returned to them. Wonder Woman must find and return the princess to the aliens in 24 hours or the earth is doomed.
name: The Bridge of Crocodiles

description: This Golden Age comic features Wonder Woman granting wishes for aiding America and includes guest appearances by Superboy, Wonder Girl and more!
name: The Chest of Monsters
The Invasion of the Sphinx Creatures

description: Wonder Woman and Steve Trevor are on the hunt for runaway balloons in "The Monster Express!"
name: The Monster Express

description: Wonder Woman and Steve Trevor investigate a graveyard of shipwrecks, while Angle Man uses his new weapon, Animox, to animate the figureheads on all the ships to attack Wonder Woman.
name: The Graveyard of Monster Ships

description: When Mer-Boy tries to get a legendary necklace from a sea spider's cave for Wonder Girl, she ends up having to rescue him.
name: The Cave of Secret Adventures

description: Wonder Woman tells the Holliday Girls a story about the Fantastic Fishermen of the Forbidden Sea and how they tried to "fish" for Wonder Woman.
name: The Fantastic Fishermen of the Forbidden Sea

description: Steve Rogers convinces himself that the real reason that Wonder Woman will not marry him is that there is someone else. The next time she travels to Paradise Island he follows her to find out if he has a rival for her affections.
name: Wonder Woman's Impossible Decision

description: In this issue, find out whether it's the Amazonian equipment that makes Wonder Woman who she is, or if she's Wonder Woman with or without it.
name: Mer-Boy's Secret Prize

description: Wonder Woman faces a fiery villain in "The Secret of Volcano Mountain!
name: The Secret of Volcano Mountain

description: Queen Hippolyta leads an Amazon fleet against invaders from Pluto, and Wonder Woman watches her mother's victory on a view-screen tuned to the past.
name: The Island Eater

description: The Sinister Seer of Saturn seeks revenge against Wonder Woman for having been deposed and exiled!
name: The Skyscraper Wonder Woman
